section.p:
CML data can also be embedded in the HTML page. The "format" parameter
      must be specfied with the value "cmlString", and the model contains the
      string CML data which encoded with the approriate HTML entities. The
      following applet displays the same molecule as above, but the CML data is
      embedded rather than in a file.


<APPLET CODE="org.openscience.jmol.applet.JmolApplet"
    ARCHIVE="jmol-applet.jar,vecmath1.1-1.12.jar,
      cdk-cml.jar,gnujaxp-saxonly.jar"
    WIDTH="200" HEIGHT="200">
  <PARAM NAME="format" VALUE="cmlString"/>
  <PARAM NAME="model" VALUE="&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; ?&gt;
&lt;!DOCTYPE molecule
  SYSTEM &quot;http://www.xml-cml.org/dtd/cml1_0.dtd&quot; []&gt;
&lt;molecule id=&quot;METHANOL&quot;&gt;
  &lt;atomArray&gt;
    &lt;stringArray builtin=&quot;id&quot;&gt;
      a1 a2 a3 a4 a5 a6
    &lt;/stringArray&gt;
    &lt;stringArray builtin=&quot;elementType&quot;&gt;
      C O H H H H
    &lt;/stringArray&gt;
    &lt;floatArray builtin=&quot;x3&quot; units=&quot;pm&quot;&gt;
      -0.748 0.558 -1.293 -1.263 -0.699 0.716
    &lt;/floatArray&gt;
    &lt;floatArray builtin=&quot;y3&quot; units=&quot;pm&quot;&gt;
      -0.015 0.420 0.202 0.754 -0.934 1.404
    &lt;/floatArray&gt;
    &lt;floatArray builtin=&quot;z3&quot; units=&quot;pm&quot;&gt;
      0.024 -0.278 -0.901 0.600 0.609 0.137
    &lt;/floatArray&gt;
  &lt;/atomArray&gt;
&lt;/molecule&gt;"/>
</APPLET>

appletParameterList.param:
Specifies custom actions to be performed by custom buttons. An
example: Button1 { HOME; FRAME=n; ROTATE=y,x,y; ZOOM=n; TRANSLATE=x,y
}  Button2 { HOME; ZOOM=n; ... } ...
